@param vm: io.availe.kreplicadocs.model.view.GuideViewModel

<p>
    The final layer in the generated code is the implementation of "global" variant interfaces, such as
    <code>KReplicaDataVariant&lt;V&gt;</code>. Every `Data` class generated by KReplica, regardless of its schema, will
    implement
    this common interface.
</p>
<p>
    These interfaces serve as a low-level hook for creating highly generic, reusable abstractions that can operate on
    any KReplica-generated model.
</p>
!{ val globalVariantsTabs = vm.tabs["generated-code-global-variants"] }
@if(globalVariantsTabs != null)
    @template.tags.tabs(tabs = globalVariantsTabs)
@endif
<p>
    The primary use case for these global interfaces is to enable patterns like the <a href="#patterns-api-mappers">Type-Safe
        API Mappers</a>. By using `KReplicaDataVariant` as a generic constraint, a mapper can be written once and
    applied to any model you define. While you may not interact with these interfaces directly very often, they are the
    foundation that makes KReplica's most advanced patterns possible.
</p>